Fountain Description/Location: By 15 Mech Engineering Research Lab. A button has dislodged from the machine.
Flavor Description: There is a slight aftertaste that doesn't last for too long. Cold. Due to location it will probably be cold year-round. Mineral flavor.

Fountain Description/Location: Copper erosion and rust around faucet
Flavor Description: Really good and very cold
Other: You have to get too close to the faucet.

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of Zips Electric and bathroom
Flavor Description: Same as above but slightly worse. I think because we let it run for a bit. We think the water might not be perfectly clear... IT SMELLS THOUGH. Just when we touch metal?

Fountain Description/Location: Located outside of B207 not by flow

Fountain Description/Location: Floor E outside of bathrooms
Flavor Description: Little more metallic than its brother, but still very cold.

In between D427 and D426

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of D404
Flavor Description: Could have been colder. Metallic/tangy. Not bad taste.
Tastes like it smells.. Heavy metal taste

Fountain Description/Location: By the servers. Near stairs S-2
Outside of men's bathroom
Flavor Description: Almost cold with a subtle taste of metal after a second or two.

Right outside of elevator 4

Fountain Description/Location: In between bathrooms

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside of the elevator near the stairs, the only water fountain on this floor wing. Perfect pressure.

Fountain Description/Location: By elevator and no smoking women's restroom

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the elevator near the stairs, the only water fountain on this floor wing.
Flavor Description: Slightly less cold. Taste reminiscent of plants.

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the elevator, near the stairs, the only water fountain on the floor wing.
Flavor Description: Cold and metallic

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the elevator near the stairs. The only water fountain on this floor wing. It has a cup filler attached. The pressure is a little too high and it splashes over the side when starting.
Flavor Description: Cold, no metal, minerals

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the small elevator in the south tower, with bricks behind it. Looks like it has been moved. Too much power splashes over the side, makes a big mess.
Flavor Description: Crazy metallic but cold (Taste like a river smells), dirty

Fountain Description/Location: Next to room 380 Mechanical Equipment
Flavor Description: Cold, slightly metallic

Fountain Description/Location: Next to room 380 Mechanical Equipment
Flavor Description: Cold, very metallic

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside of the elevator near the stairs, the only water fountain on floor wing. OASIS model. Low power stream, gotta get close to the faucet (Bunch of oxygen in water). It leaks.
Flavor Description: Slightly colder than room temperature. Highly metallic.

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the small elevator in the south tower, with bricks behind it.
Flavor Description: Cold, very metallic

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of room 480
Flavor Description: Cold, delayed metal taste

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of room 480
Flavor Description: Cold, instant metal taste

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the elevator near the stairs, the only water fountain on this floor wing.
Flavor Description: Leaves a metallic aftertaste in your mouth.

Fountain Description/Location: Right outside the elevator near the stairs, the only water fountain on this floor wing. Push button doesn't work.
Flavor Description: Warm, heavy metal taste?

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of 575
Flavor Description: Slightly metallic, decently cold

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of 575. Crusty looking.
Flavor Description: As cold as 1WT, albeit slightly more metallic

Fountain Description/Location: In the atrium by the elevator
Flavor Description: Not that cold, but it's 90� outside right now and it's not hot. It has a mineral aftertaste. Not the worst, but not bad. Dylan said, "It's cold and tastes like nothing." Upon letting the fountain run for a couple of seconds, the temperature dropped drastically in the flow of the water.

Fountain Description/Location: In the atrium by the elevator
Flavor Description: Not bad. Dylan said, "It's cold and tastes like nothing." Upon letting the fountain run for a couple of seconds, the temperature dropped drastically in the flow of the water.
Other: NOTE: SPLASHES A LITTLE (Stream is a little too forceful -Dylan)

Fountain Description/Location: By the bathrooms near room 121. The water pressure is trying it's best but not working.
By the bathrooms behind room 138. Distinguished by the lack of paint above. Upon time of testing, the water bottles saved is only 13. New.
Flavor Description: Cold and tastes of cleaner type chemical.

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of room 132. Press down, NOT in. The stream is angled towards the user and thus does not fall squarely; this is due to the nozzle not being lined up with the shell around it. The optical illusion is real. Dirt in water fountain. Crackling and spurting noises. I hate it.
Flavor Description: Really Bad. Warm. Makes odd noises. Dylan: "If we are taking in the aura and the vibe of the water fountain, it is definitely an F" " Everything about it is off-putting"

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of 101 and 106, this is another push down. Dirty, rusted nozzle. You can see the copper residue on the bottom of the fountain where the water immediately falls. "If you are a penny connoisseur, come check out this fountain today!" "Drink the smell of when you rub coins across your hand."
Flavor Description: Super cold even during a hot day. Super coppery, health hazard?

Fountain Description/Location: Storage hallway, women's bathroom across from room 101. Again, push down. MOLD ON NOZZLE.
Flavor Description: Screen over nozzle, and a stream of water following. Looks like an oil spill. The water is very cold. The copper taste hits hard a couple seconds after drinking.
Other: spec is in cup. The mold and/or oxidation stuck to Dylan's finger. You can take part of the fountain home with you. we don't know what's actually in there cuz this is just the stuff that is coming up from the crevice. this could be a very big health hazard.

Fountain Description/Location: Inside the side entrance to the building, near door 10. There are brown specks all over the bottom. It's hard to push.
Flavor Description: Why does it dry out my mouth??? It's water??? Made Dylan's stomach hurt.

Fountain Description/Location: Inside the side entrance to the building, by door 10.
Flavor Description: Why does it dry out my mouth??? It's water??? Made Dylan's stomach hurt.

Fountain Description/Location: Directly exiting elevator. Lot of copper. Press down.
Flavor Description: Backrooms Water fountain. Tastes how the backrooms would smell.

Fountain Description/Location: Directly exiting elevator. Lot of copper. Press down.
Flavor Description: Penny aftertastes, but same as floor 2.

Fountain Description/Location: Outside the elevator to the right. Plugged into the wall. Divided top.
Flavor Description: Copper

Fountain Description/Location: Outside of stairwell C-T. There is blue paint and has visible plug. Drains really slow.
Flavor Description: Even tastes like paint (aftertaste) I can't be sure it was the water, but it probably was. I almost threw up, also almost made Dylan�s stomach hurt.

Fountain Description/Location: Located between Janitor closet 126 and Room 124. Looks clean.
Flavor Description: It has a slight metal taste, but is decently cool. This water fountain phases between tasting like metal and tasting like regular water, so hopefully you catch it at the right time.
Other: Splashes you slightly when turned on.

Fountain Description/Location: Located between Janitor closet 126 and Room 124. Looks clean and has a green filter status.
Flavor Description: Tastes like neutral water, but nothing impressive.

Fountain Description/Location: Located between the Mail Room 118 and Media Services Satellite room. It looks very shiny, but the nozzle has some green corrosion on it.
Flavor Description: Very cold after you give it a bit to warm up (I swear there was something on my tongue after I drank that - Dylan) "saving Grace is how cold it is" there is some sort of metal aftertaste but we don't know what metal because it's not just like basic copper.
Other: Pressing the button is very noisy

Fountain Description/Location: Located between the snack room and 108 janitor room. The water fountain looks pretty clean. It has a little bit of green on the nozzle, but not as much as the water fountain previously.
Flavor Description: Dylan thinks it is warm and metallic, Tabby thinks it is warm and mineraly goodness. Dylan again feels something on his tongue after drinking this water fountain.
Other: missing two screws on one side

Fountain Description/Location: Located between room 124 and stairwell A. It is missing the drain cover.
Flavor Description: "Literally perfect. Cold and not metallic and good!" - Tabby. "Made my stomach feel weird and tasted bitter" - Dylan
Other: Doesn't flow far from the dispenser so you have to get close

Fountain Description/Location: Located directly outside of staircase A.
Flavor Description: Dried out Dylan's mouth. A little bit better than average, it's pretty cold.

Fountain Description/Location: Located between rooms 272 and 235.
Flavor Description: "A lot of Mineraly stuff that I don't like. It tastes like you're drinking out of like a paper cup or through a paper straw when it's disintegrating." - Tabby. "It tasted like the way that the food in Chipotle smells." - Dylan

Fountain Description/Location: Located between room 371 and room 325.
Flavor Description: Very cold but tastes really bad... "The coldness is the only saving grace."

Fountain Description/Location: Located directly outside of staircase A, it has a very fancy long handle. It gives off a vibe of "I'm better than every other fountain".
Flavor Description: Flow inconsistent. The nozzle smells musty. "Made my mouth feel powdery" - Dylan. Tabby thinks that it tasted like bad minerals; also, it was not very cold. Dylan thinks it tasted good though.
Other: it has a mechanically whirling loose fan sound. The elongated handle wags when you let go of it. You have to get really close to the spigot in order to drink the water that flows out of it. it feels like when you hold your pinky up when you're drinking tea.
